00:00:12.400 --> 00:00:14.490
SHANE SMITH: So after traveling
across Siberia on

00:00:14.490 --> 00:00:17.410
one train, deep into the middle
of nowhere, we switched

00:00:17.410 --> 00:00:20.110
to another train going
even deeper into

00:00:20.110 --> 00:00:21.440
the middle of nowhere.

00:00:21.440 --> 00:00:24.480
And finally, after two and a
half very drunken days on the

00:00:24.480 --> 00:00:27.290
train, we arrived in Tynda,
where the North Korean

00:00:27.290 --> 00:00:28.762
administrative camp was.

00:00:36.970 --> 00:00:39.280
So we just got to Tynda.

00:00:39.280 --> 00:00:43.080
Some say it's the worst town
in all of Russia--

00:00:43.080 --> 00:00:44.440
the most depressing.

00:00:44.440 --> 00:00:48.020
And we're actually going to try
to go to the office that

00:00:48.020 --> 00:00:51.950
runs all the North Koreans in
the region and see if we can

00:00:51.950 --> 00:00:53.200
ask them some questions.

00:00:59.180 --> 00:01:01.920
We met this cop on the train.

00:01:01.920 --> 00:01:03.050
He seemed liked a nice guy.

00:01:03.050 --> 00:01:07.110
He got the thugs away from us
when things got a bit drunk-y.

00:01:07.110 --> 00:01:10.220
And so then he's offered to
help us, which is good.

00:01:10.220 --> 00:01:12.540
Because when we went to the
hotel to check in, we

00:01:12.540 --> 00:01:13.260
didn't check in.

00:01:13.260 --> 00:01:13.630
Why?

00:01:13.630 --> 00:01:18.860
Because the FSB, who used to be
the KGB, are asking about

00:01:18.860 --> 00:01:21.410
us, saying, let us know
when they check in.

00:01:21.410 --> 00:01:23.650
So the lady said, I'll let them
know, but I'm letting you

00:01:23.650 --> 00:01:25.250
know that I'm letting
them know.

00:01:25.250 --> 00:01:27.420
So we're like, OK, we won't
be staying there.

00:01:27.420 --> 00:01:30.370
So we stayed in an apartment
where the water

00:01:30.370 --> 00:01:31.490
smelled like gasoline.

00:01:31.490 --> 00:01:34.110
And now we have a cop that we're
going to bring with us,

00:01:34.110 --> 00:01:37.755
so we seem more official when we
go meet the North Koreans.

00:01:51.260 --> 00:01:53.550
We just got here, and
we see posters

00:01:53.550 --> 00:01:55.510
of Kim Il-Sung already.

00:01:55.510 --> 00:01:58.850
And also it says here that they
will lay their lives down

00:01:58.850 --> 00:02:03.200
for the revolution of the great
leader, Kim Jong-Il.

00:02:03.200 --> 00:02:04.720
What are we waiting
for, by the way?

